Interface TransactionLogHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultTransactionLogHandler

    public interface TransactionLogHandler
    The bean used to log the transactions between the DNSAPIClient instances and the DNSAPI server.
    Author:
    Chris Wright
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • logTransaction

        void logTransaction(Object command,
                  Object response,
                  CommandMetaData commandMetaData)
        Logs a successful transaction between a DNSAPIClient instance and the DNSAPI server.
        Parameters:
        command - The command sent from the DNSAPIClient to the DNSAPI server.
        response - The response sent back from the DNSAPI server to the DNSAPIClient.
        commandMetaData - The additional information for the transaction.

      • logFailedTransaction

        void logFailedTransaction(Object command,
                        Throwable exception,
                        CommandMetaData commandMetaData)

        Parameters:
        command - The command sent from the DNSAPIClient to the DNSAPI server.
        exception - The exception sent back from the DNSAPI server to the DNSAPIClient.
        commandMetaData - The additional information for the transaction.
